{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive|qq=}}
'''Yin Earth Snake also known as å·ąå·ģ''' (tsuchinotomi, kidonomi, kishi) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|å­ååđēæŊ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}}.

It is the 6th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|å­ååđēæŊ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sexagenary cycle|qq=}}, preceded by {{ill|Boshin|ja|æčū°|1=Yang Earth Dragon|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Boshin|qq=}} and followed by {{ill|Kougo|ja|åšå|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kougo|qq=}}. In the context of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|é°é―äščĄææģ|1=Yin-Yang and Wuxing Theory|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|qq=}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|ååđē|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Heavenly Stems|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Ki|ja|å·ą|1=Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Earth|ja|å|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earth|qq=}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|åäšæŊ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Earthly Branches|qq=}} symbol {{ill|Snake|ja|å·ģ|1=Snake (zodiac)|lt=Snake (å·ģ)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Snake|13=User:Immanuelle/Snake (zodiac)|qq=}} represents yin {{ill|Fire|ja|įŦ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fire|qq=}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|äščĄææģ#įļįïžãããããïž|lt=Mutual Generation|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mutual Generation|qq=}}) (i.e. Fire gives rise to Earth).

