===Events=== * {{ill|Kishii Kikou|ja|å·ąå·ģįīčĄ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii Kikou|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii Kikou|qq=}}: a travelogue of the western regions compiled by [[:en:Kaibara Ekken|Kaihara Ekken]] in [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 2 (1689 AD), notable for being the first known instance of the term [[:en:Three Views of Japan|Japanâs Three Views]]. (As annotated in ãæ°æĨæŽåĪå ļæå­ĶåĪ§įģŧã by {{ill|Itasaka Youko|ja|æŋåčå­|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itasaka Youko|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Itasaka Youko|qq=}}, Iwanami Shoten, 1991) ==Months of Yin Earth Snake== ==Yin Earth Snake (å·ąå·ģ)'s Months== In a [[:en:Common Era|Common Era]] year whose final digit is 4 or 9 (when the [[:en:Heavenly Stems|Heavenly Stems]] are {{ill|Kou|ja|įē|1=Kinoe (įē)|lt=Kinoe (įē)|2=ja|3=įē|4=zh|5=įē|1=Kinoe (įē)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kou|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoe (įē)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kou|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinoe (įē)|qq=}} or {{ill|Ki|ja|å·ą|1=Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|lt=Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|2=ja|3=å·ą|4=zh|5=å·ą|1=Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ki|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchinoto (å·ą)|qq=}}), the month of [[:en:April|April]] is designated as the [[:en:Month|month (calendar)]] of {{ill|Kishii|ja|1=Yin Earth Snake|å·ąå·ģ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Earth Snake|qq=}}. However, here the term "month" may refer either to the month of the {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|æ§æĶ|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} or to the [[:en:Solar term|Solar term]] (from [[:en:Lixia|Lixia]] until the day before [[:en:Mangzhong|Mangzhong]]) as applicable. ==Days of Yin Earth Snake== ==Yin Earth Snake (å·ąå·ģ)'s Days== The {{ill|selected day|ja|éļæĨ|1=Senjitsu|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/selected day|13=User:Immanuelle/Senjitsu|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/selected day|13=User:Immanuelle/Senjitsu|qq=}} for {{ill|Kishii|ja|1=Yin Earth Snake|å·ąå·ģ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Earth Snake|qq=}} is as follows. ==={{nihongo|selection days|éļæĨ|senjitsu|qq=}}=== The day of {{ill|Kishii|ja|1=Yin Earth Snake|å·ąå·ģ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishii|13=User:Immanuelle/Yin Earth Snake|qq=}} is the 2nd day of {{ill|Small Earth|ja|įŊå|lt=Small Earth|lt_ja=å°å|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Small Earth|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Small Earth|qq=}}. ===æĶæģĻäļæŪĩ=== * For {{ill|Lunisolar|ja|æ§æĶ|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lunisolar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}} months of April, June, or October, it is an {{ill|Unlucky Assembly Day|ja|åķäžæĨ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unlucky Assembly Day|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Unlucky Assembly Day|qq=}}. * {{ill|Divine Auspicious Day|ja|įĨåæĨ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Auspicious Day|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Divine Auspicious Day|qq=}} * {{ill|Great Bright Day|ja|åĪ§ææĨ|qq=draft|qq=draft|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Bright Day|qq=|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Great Bright Day|qq=}}
